I think that most quests which were in place before the creation of the epic quests can go trivial (Soulfire quest, monk headband and sash quest, etc.)<br>
<br>
As far as I know most of the epic quest stuff that was put in the game just for the epic quest was exempted from trivial loot code.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how this applies to needed dropped items that existed before the epic quests were put into place, they will probably go trivial too.  The safest thing is to look up the information on your epic quest early and make sure you get those things you need before they go trivial, which of course could take away from the fun of discovery, but keeps you safe from the horrors of having to buy it at huge markups in the bazaar (or from forcing your lower level friends to do it for you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
